New Records: Travis Head scored an unbeaten 154, his highest ODI score, coming off 129 balls with 20 fours and five sixes
Key Match Events: England collapsed to 315 all out with two balls unused after being 213 for two in the 33rd over
Travis Head made an unbeaten century and power Australia to a seven-wicket win
Australia reached 317-3 with six overs to spare
Pre-Game Insights: Harry Brook spoke to BBC after the game, and he suggests that “it probably went wrong at the toss when I batted first”
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Brook says that England “did everything we said we were going to do”
Stuart Broad calls Travis Head an “incredible player” across all three formats
Miscellaneous Highlights: Australia's World Cup final hero needed no second invitation and crashed 20 fours and five sixes
Travis Head makes England pay with superb century in seven-wicket Australia win
